      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus drawn from certified material test reports for the production lot used in bench testing. Screw and rod geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of three representative specimens. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo sampling (n=500 draws) across material property and geometric tolerance distributions; combined UQ declared at package level. A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development ranked cortical modulus and screw-rod friction coefficient as dominant variance contributors to stiffness QoI, confirming that input characterization effort was appropriately focused. Level 3 achieved."
